President Donald Trump issued a proclamation on May 10, 2018, recognizing the important role military spouses play in the defense of the country. Military Spouse Day is a day to honor and thank these individuals for their selfless support and significant contributions. The proclamation acknowledges the sacrifices military spouses make, including frequent moves, separations, and the challenges they face in finding employment. The administration is committed to improving employment opportunities for military spouses, including through an executive order enhancing opportunities for military spouses in the federal government. The proclamation also encourages American businesses to employ military spouses and highlights the Department of Defense's Military Spouse Employment Partnership. The proclamation calls on the people of the United States to honor military spouses with appropriate ceremonies and activities.